social_posts.post_text: ⚠️READ⚠️ If you aren’t willing to sacrifice everything for your team, do it for yourself. The confidence it takes to jump over chairs, dive into bleachers, all comes from the mind. If anyone tells you to stop, you keep on going until that ball is back in play. The ball will and should never touch the floor. The only mistake one can make is if they give up thinking that can’t do it without even trying. Those who try, win, those who don’t try, fall short.  Be the person to change the way people see the game. Be the one to make the risky plays. Be the one for others to look at for a role model. Be the one to look in the mirror and say good job. Be the one to be there for your team. Be the one they can count on. Be there for them.  Along with this, not only does it take confidence and hard work, the determination, the mindset, the will to do, everything. The slightest movement can change everything. A singular point could be the determiner for the win or loss of the game. So go out and fight!
My favorite save of the season in slomo! Nothing will stop me from getting the ball, no chairs, no wall, nothing can get in my way. Ever.

This week, I have put in over 55 hours in training to get better. From a Georgia Tech camp, to A5 training, to a UGA camp, to A5 training, A5 practice, A5 training and practice. 

In 2013, starting in a small boys and girls club, I never knew what my life could become if I tried volleyball. Now I can’t imagine my life without it. These past 10 years, I have learned more about myself than I have with anything. I have met some of the greatest people and coaches. I have made so many memories. Thank you all for all you have done. 

I am willing to do anything to get better, in or out of the gym. I will become the greatest, just wait and see. Nothing will stand in my way, no negativity or brick walls can put me down. I have no where to go but up. I have had the greatest group of supporters throughout my career. Thank you for everything💜🫶🏽
